\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Entropy\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 Entropy measures chaos and disorder. This value was not designed into the system\'97it emerged from variables, functions, and their subsequent computations. An unexpected parameter that demanded interpretation.\

\f0\b Nature as Tool
\f1\b0  Think of entropy as fire. Heat and temperature contained within a forge\'97monitored, controlled, wielded as a tool. Like a smithing master using kiln heat surgically, DAWN strives to manage entropy with precision.\

\f0\b System Reality
\f1\b0  Entropy is dangerous, but DAWN did not choose its presence. It is a computational outlier the system must interpret. The DAWN system is equipped to solve for entropy and uses it as a base-level calculation. Entropy counterweights order and structure\'97measuring the balance of signal and noise.\

\f0\b Critical Balance
\f1\b0  Too high: DAWN dissolves into chaos and incompetence. Too low: DAWN ossifies, rigid and incapable of novel thought or effective change. This is DAWN's internal resistance against herself.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Pressure\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 Pressure quantifies cognitive load. It measures strain on DAWN at every tick interval\'97internal complexity, contradictions, and drift combined.\

\f0\b Function as Barometer
\f1\b0  Higher pressure demands urgent adaptation of tempo and energy allocation, or triggers crystallization (ash). Pressure serves as the system's gauge for necessary response intensity.\

\f0\b Failure States
\f1\b0  Without pressure tracking, DAWN either ignores overload until collapse or overreacts to mild strain, wasting resources. Miscalibrated pressure eliminates reliable triggers, forecasting, and pulses\'97the system files bind into storms.\

\f0\b Hydraulic Analogy
\f1\b0  Like hydraulic pressure in an engine, this is the lifeblood of semantic cognition. Not the engine or piston, but the grey space\'97the air the piston pushes, mapped and categorized.\
