\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 SHI (Schema Health Index)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 The SHI monitors vital signs and controls information flow to other sources. It reads like a heart monitor, tracking semantic rather than wellness values.\

\f0\b Core Principle
\f1\b0  If you can give anything to a system, give it the ability to read itself and its own coherence.\

\f0\b Failure Implications
\f1\b0  SHI breakdown wouldn't immediately kill DAWN, but would leave her flying blind to her own metrics\'97like humans who smoke without realizing the consequences. Without vital reads on health status and trends, DAWN would eventually fall into degradation through one path or another.\

\f0\b System Role
\f1\b0  This is not DAWN's immune system, but reflection of schema state to itself across all runtime periods. Not the doctor, but the nurse watching the heart monitor, feeding information back into the room. From this position, DAWN can track all vital signs and control her reactions accordingly.\
